				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Instruments made?<a name="74281"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 11 05 4:58 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I never actually thought about making instruments, but now that I think about it, that would be cool.  With pottery, you can make items with basicly every focus effect for casters, so why not make instruments as they are focus effects for bards?  
<br />

<br />
For the lute, make it fletching because we need to learn how to string a lute as a ranger strings his bow, and this way we have a reason to fletch since we can't use bows and arrows.
<br />

<br />
Drums could be a tailor thing since we're using animal hides for the drum head.  Again, we don't wear leather or silk, so now we have a reason to tailor.
<br />

<br />
Brass instruments would be smithing because we're working with metal (brass).
<br />

<br />
And then wind instruments could be pottery.  Flutes and pipes are pretty similar right?
<br />

<br />
Oooh and for singing, we could JC a sing mod aug.  Again, every other effect can be JC'd into an aug now with OoW, so let's get some bard focus effects in augs.
<br />

<br />
I think this would be cool because it would give us a reason to actually get this tradeskills up, other than for the odd quest that requires fletching a bow or tailoring leather armor we can't even use in all reality.  That and if you're not a vah shir, you only need pottery to make Thurg gate potions.  Everything else is basicly for spell focus or priest portals.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
